text:
Spanning over the Sungei Seletar, Née Soon Bridge was built by Public Works Department replacing the old wooden bridge.
The bridge and Née Soon Road serve as a main access road to the residents of the Springleaf estate.

Used to be a wooden bridge many years ago before it was rebuilt to its current state.
2 way traffic for vehicle to pass through and there was a walkway for pedestrians as well.

Good position to view the pond/lake from the bridge.
